    "Conversely, LSTMs are particularly suited for tasks requiring the management of longterm dependencies within sequential data (Hou et al. 2020).",
    "In fossil image analysis, LSTMs excel at tracking detailed changes across a series of images, such as variations in fossil features over time or from different angles.",
    "By effectively handling long-range dependencies, LSTMs can enhance feature extraction from temporal image datasets and improve the classification accuracy of fossils, providing a more comprehensive analysis of their characteristics.",
    "Transformers represent a significant advancement in modeling sequential data by introducing a novel self-attention mechanism, which contrasts with traditional approaches like RNNs and LSTMs.",
    "Unlike RNNs, which process data in a sequential manner, Transformers leverage parallel processing to handle long-range dependencies efficiently (Turner 2023)."
